description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a qualified anatomical pathology technologist to join an energetic mortuary team at the Northern Care Alliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have the Level 3 Diploma in Anatomical Pathology Technology, or the RSPH Certificate and Diploma in Anatomical Pathology Technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a person with excellent technical and communication skills and an ability to work with people of all levels and backgrounds. A robust knowledge of best practice mortuary health and safety practices is essential. You will be well organised and able to work under pressure and to tight deadlines, sometimes with little supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as part of the mortuary team across the trust, and will be supported to develop your skills and experience in both areas. The department provides specialist neuropathology and forensic neuropathology services to Salford Royal Hospital and the wider region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michael Coombes&lt;br /&gt;Mortuary Operations Manager&lt;br /&gt;michael.Coombes@srft.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;0161 206 4484&lt;/p&gt;
